Kylian Mbappe’s mother, Fayza Lamari, has insisted that her son will have control of his image rights at Real Madrid should he eventually joins the LaLiga champions this summer. Lamari said this while providing an update on Mbappe’s future at Paris Saint-Germain. According to her, Mbappe has reached an agreement with PSG and Real Madrid and must now make his final decision over which club he will play for next season. Mbappe’s current contract with PSG will expire at the end of the season. The France international is yet to sign a new contract with PSG and has been heavily linked with a move to Real Madrid this summer. However, Lamari has now delivered an update on her son’s situation as the 23-year-old forward prepares to announce his next career move. “We will not have new meetings to discuss Mbappe’s future, these meetings are now over,” Lamari told Kora Plus. “Now we have found an agreement with both Real Madrid and PSG and the discussions are over because it’s Kylian [Mbappe]who has to choose now. “The two offers, that of PSG and Real [Madrid], are almost identical. At Real, my son will have control of his image rights! We will now await his decision. “In the Real Madrid offer we’ve full power of image rights, on the other hand there is an economic balance that rewards this thing, in short there is no difference between the two are similar.”